The Nigerian army has said the concept of establishing the Special Army Super IV camp in the north-west zone was to crush unrepentant bandits, explaining that the unit has been supporting the troops to protect lives and properties. This was disclosed by the deputy commandant and Director of studies, National Defense College, Man. Gen Elias Attu in Faskari, Katsina State during a media interactive session. “The sustenance of the camp has already been assured because the camp was specifically designed to deal with strategic issues. The troops have been getting mutual support from other sister agencies and individuals ” “We are also working together with other stakeholders for quality information which has helped us to achieve a lot” “Nigerian army has the constitutional responsibility to ensure the total protection of the country ” “We will ensure that the logistics in the camp is properly distributed”